features: 【EXTRA LARGE】With two large and two medium round holders, this utensil caddy can hold 30-40 kitchen tools, easily categorize different utensils in different compartments, store your spatulas, forks, knives, tongs, chopsticks, spoons, ladles, whisks, peelers, turners, flatware, silverware and more in the manner that suits you best, ensuring easy access and no more searching for the right tool while cooking

【DETACHABLE DESIGN】The four wire baskets and the base are connected through magnetic, so you can take out any one as needed. The base consists of two pieces that can be installed together as a whole or separated into two parts to match with the holders individually. This avoids the inconvenience of lifting the entire holder and makes it more flexible and portable

【ALL OPEN STYLE】Wire utensil holder makes the inside visible and open to air, no musty odor, no water accumulation, help utensils to dry quickly and efficiently, also perfect for busy cooks who need to quickly identify their preferred utensils at a glance during cooking. The open and removable design makes cleaning a breeze, with no worries about hidden corners or stubborn stains

【DURABLE & STYLISH】The baskets are made of sturdy metal, while the base is crafted from natural weighted bamboo with a water-resistant coating, additionally come with adhesive rubber feets. This fully ensures stability and avoids tipping when picking out utensils. Its compact design allows it to fit in any corner of kitchen without taking up space. The elegant black metal and rustic bamboo add a modern and classic touch, suitable for various home styles

【VERSATILE STORAGE】This is not only a kitchen utensil organizer, also a perfect cutlery holder for picnic, camping, BBQ, buffet, parties, bar, RV and gatherings. You can choose to use one, two, or all of the cylindrical holders as needed. Additionally, it can also serve as a storage container for your dining table, cabinets, or pantry, helping you organize small items in your study or bedroom, such as pens and stationery

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Seam In The Middle Is Not Quite Even
reviews.reviewText: I am very OCD. I am always slightly worried about items that are some assembly required as they tend not to line up perfectly or be perfectly straight when done. Which does bother me more than I would like. This specifically looks like one piece in the picture but is actually two pieces you have to screw together in the middle. For that reason the middle is not 100% straight but does sit very flat on a surface. The included metal tubes fit in the spaces perfectly and are slightly magnetic so they stay in place. The magnet is not super strong so you won't disturb the rest of the containers when you go to remove one.Overall it is a nice sturdy piece and holds all my silverware and utensils like I wanted but for someone who is super OCD like me you might want to pass as the middle won't be even and it isn't on solid base.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Clearly designed to prioritize cheaper shipping
reviews.reviewText: This design of this product was to optimize shipping above all else. The bottom bamboo base is not a single piece, but 2 pieces that you have to attach by drilling in a metal plate. It will likely not be flush and has a cheaper look to it. I'm sure this is done to keep the shipping box smaller. Additionally, the individual metal baskets are not uniform in size. There are two smaller ones and 2 larger ones so they could fit into each other which I suspect is also for shipping purposes.That being said, the base seems to be made of bamboo. The magnets in the base are also helpful in keeping the baskets secure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars holds what I need it to.
reviews.reviewText: I am trying to re-organize my kitchen. It is a very small, '70s galley-style kitchen and has very little in the way of counter space. One thing that I needed to find a solution to was the fact that the (plastic) drawer that I used for utensils recently shattered from old age...so I need to find a space-efficient but functional way to store my utensils stove-side. This is working well for me. It doesn't hold a TON of them, but it DOES hold enough for my needs in the way of wooden spoons, spatulas, scrapers and such.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really like this organizer! I had been keeping my utensils in about 6-7 cups on my counter and it was taking up a considerable account of counter space. After receiving this organizer, I washed up the metal cups and put all the utensils I had on my counter into this organizer and they all fit! Not only that, it takes up a fraction of the space I was using before.One thing I wish is that the cups were interchangeable with each other, because I could've had the bigger ones on the outside instead of in the middle. Besides this, I really like this organizer and it has really helped clean up my counter. I highly recommend.
